content: SIX! TIM SEIFERT FINISHES IT IN FINE FASHION! Floated full, outside off. Tim Seifert gets low and smokes it over the wide long-off fence for another maximum to get the job done. He ends with an unbeaten 97 off just 38 balls. New Zealand win by 8 wickets with 10 overs to spare and take the series 4-1.
SIX MORE! INCREDIBLE STRIKING! Floated up outside off. Tim Seifert clears the front leg and slog sweeps high over wide long-on for a third maximum in the over.

DROPPED AND SIX! Shadab Khan bowls it slower through the air, and much wide outside off. Tim Seifert reaches for it and lofts it toward the long-off region. Haris Rauf fails to judge it and the ball bursts through his hands and palms it over the ropes for a maximum.
Floated full, around off. Daryl Mitchell heaves it off the inner half through mid-wicket region for a single.
Quicker length ball, outside off. Tim Seifert flat-bats this toward long-off for just a single.
SIX! LAUNCHED! Tossed up full, on off. Tim Seifert gets low and powers it flat over the cow corner fence for a biggie. He is a hurry to finish this.
Flatter length ball, on off. Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line and defends from the crease.
Tossed up on the middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell nudges into the leg side where the bowler runs across and stops it himself.
Flatter googly, around off. Dabbed to short third for one.
Tossed up on the middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell eases it past the bowler and down to long-on for one.

OUT! STUMPED! Sufiyan Muqeem gets his man! Delivers it full and quick, on the leg stump line. Mark Chapman looks to jam it but the ball comes off his pad and goes toward the keeper. Mohammad Haris behind the stumps is quick to take off the bails as Mark Chapman loses his balance and his foot is out of the crease. Sufiyan Muqeem has his second wicket as Chapman departs early.
Mark Chapman st M Haris b S Muqeem 3 (7b 0x4 0x6)

Bowls it full and quick on the middle and leg stump line. Mark Chapman gets low for the swipe but the ball skids through and hits him in front. An appeal from Pakistan and up goes the finger. Mark Chapman has gone upstairs for the review. The ball tracking shows that the impact is outside the line and Chapman survives.
FOUR! PUMPED! Dropped short, outside off. Tim Seifert gets on top of the bounce and slaps it toward deep extra cover region. One bounce and over the ropes.
Flatter leg break, outside off. Tim Seifert cuts it to the point fielder.
Tossed up on off. Mark Chapman eases this through covers for a single.

DROPPED! Shortish leg break, on the middle and leg stump line. Mark Chapman goes back and pulls it straight to the throat of Usman Khan at the deep square leg region. He shells down the simple chance. Mark Chapman gets a lifeline.
Banged in short and quick on off. Tim Seifert swats it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter leg break, on the middle and leg. Mark Chapman backs away and chips it past the left of the bowler for a single.
Pushed through quicker, and flatter, on off. Tim Seifert plays across the line and gets the inside edge onto the pad.  A tidy over from Sufiyan Muqeem.
Wrong'un, slower through the air, outside off. Tim Seifert goes back and pulls it toward wide of long-on for a couple. A misfield in the deep allows the second run.
Touch short and quick outside off. Mark Chapman cuts this to deep point for a single to get off the mark.
Flatter leg break, around off. Mark Chapman cuts it to backward point.

OUT! BOWLED'EM! Sufiyan Muqeem gets the breakthrough! Bowls it flat and quick on the off-stump line. Finn Allen looks to pull this over the leg side but the ball skids through and hits the top of the off-stump. A breezy cameo from Finn Allen comes to an end.
Finn Allen b S Muqeem 27 (12b 5x4 1x6)
Tossed up full, on off. Tim Seifert slog-sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Slower bumper, on the middle. Tim Seifert is early into the shot and miscues the pull in front of deep square leg fielder for a single. 25 runs coming off the over.

SIX! THIRD SIX OF THE OVER! Back of a length delivery on the middle stump line. Tim Seifert picks the length and smokes it over deep square leg fence, into the stands for another maximum. This is now the highest powerplay score by New Zealand.
Good length delivery on the middle and leg. Tim Seifert heaves it off the inner half of the blade toward deep backward square leg. Abdul Samad puts the dive in the deep and saves a couple.
SIX! FIFTY FOR TIM SEIFERT! The carnage continues. Back of a length delivery on off. Tim Seifert makes room and slaps it over deep cover boundary for half a dozen.

FOUR! BANG! Short of a length delivery around off. Tim Seifert picks the length and smacks it toward the deep mid-wicket region. One bounce and into the boundary. Tim Seifert is in no mood to stop tonight.
SIX! Jahandad Khan is greeted back with a biggie! Slower ball on a length, on the middle. Tim Seifert picks the change of pace and hammers it over deep mid-wicket for an 83m hit.
FOUR! On a length wide outside off, Finn Allen looks to slog this towards leg but gets an outside edge and the ball has gone past the keeper's right for four.
Good length into the body, Tim Seifert tucks this to mid on and takes one.
Bumper, around off. Tim Seifert leaves it all alone. This has been a good over, SO FAR.
Good length on off, Tim Seifert blocks it out. A rare sight watching Tim Seifert block one.
Short-pitched, around off, Tim Seifert smashes this to extra cover for no run.
FOUR! Innovative from Tim Seifert. On a length wide outside off, Tim Seifert shuffles across and ramps this over short fine leg for a boundary to begin the 5th over.
Good length on top of middle, Finn Allen defends this out.

FOUR! A bit better in terms of timing from Allen but still not the most convincing stroke. PItched-up around off, Finn Allen lofts this over cover for four more. The bat tilts in his hands again but he gets enough behind it to take it away to the fence.
FOUR! On a length around off, Finn Allen gets right behind the line of it and lofts this over cover for a boundary. Finn Allen did not time this well enough but still manages to find the fence.
On a length arond leg, Tim Seifert flicks this to deep mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! A poor fielding effort from the fielder at third man region and this has raced to the fence for four. On a length wide of off, Tim Seifert swings and gets a top edge past third man fro four.

WOW! Proper Pakistan stuff these 3.1 overs have been. Shades of brilliance sandwiched in between some really poor bowling. Good length, on off, shaping a fraction away after pitching. Tim Seifert had no answers to it as he gets beaten on the outside.
On a length around off, Tim Seifert drives this to cover and takes one.

A proper fast bowler's response. Bumper, shaping into the batter. Tim Seifert manages to somehow get away from this. This was fast and right at the badge on the helmet but Tim Seifert does well to escape from it.

SIX! OH DEAR ME! This has gone deep into the crowd for a huge six. On a length, in the slot, Tim Seifert clears his front leg and slogs this right out of the middle of his bat and this has comfortably cleared the fence for a huge six.
FOUR! Good length down the leg, Tim Seifert flicks this fine and wide to the right of short fine for a boundary.
Good length wide of off, Finn Allen pushes this to mid off and takes a quick single.
Good length around middle and leg, Tim Seifert tucks this to deep square for one.
SIX! A biggie to end the over and 14 comes off this one. Good length on the pads, Finn Allen swivels back and just flick this all the way, into the stands toward deep square for a huge six.
On a length around off, shaping away from the batter. Finn Allen looks to poke at it and gets beaten.

FOUR! Not that convincing from Allen but a boundary to him. Back of a length around off, Finn Allen runs down the track and swings at it. Gets a top edge and the ball has sailed over first slip for a boundary towards the third man region.
Good length around off, Finn Allen blocks it out on off for another dot.

A bit more traditional from Mohammad Ali as he lands one on that nagging length around off and takes it away looking to get an outside edge but Finn Allen keeps his bat closer to his body and manges to get beaten on the outside.
FOUR! Short-pitched, around middle and leg, Finn Allen pulls this over mid-wicket and the ball has raced away to the fence for four.
SIX! Ends the over with a biggie. Good length around off, Tim Seifert shuffles to his leg and lofts this over cover for a huge six. Tim Seifert looks in a hurry to wrap things up.
Away swinger this time, Tim Seifert swings at it but gets beaten on the outside.

SIX! Business as usual for Tim Seifert as he clears the fence for the first time in this game. Pitched-up on the pads, swinging it into the batter. Tim Seifert flicks this and deposits it into the stands towards deep square for six.

FOUR! That's the form Tim Seifert is carrying into the contest. Pitched-up around off, Tim Seifert settles well inside his crease, presents a full face of his bat and just punches this down the ground to long off for four.
WIDE! Another extra and it is wide this time. On a length down the leg, Tim Seifert moves in and looks to ramp but misses. Wided

Jahandad Khan gets away with the free hit as he bowls a dot. Good length on the pads, swinging into the batter. Tim Seifert looks to clear the fence towards deep square but gets an inside edge onto his pads for no run.
NO BALL! A good delivery, which was a dot initially, but the third umpire checks this and calls it a no ball. Free hit up next for Tim Seifert.
WOAH! That is some start with the ball for Khan. Short-pitched, around the ribcage. Tim wasn't expecting it and barely managed to get away.

On a length, down the leg, Haris Rauf follows his close the ees and swing tradition, manages a top edge this time that hands over Will O'Rourke at deep third and he drops it. Three runs taken to close the inning. Pakistan have managed to post 128 on board.
Slower one, around leg again, Haris Rauf swings and misses out completely.
Short-pitched, around leg, Haris Rauf closes his eyes and swings hard at it. Misses out again.
A good slower one, wide of off, Haris Rauf swings for a pace-on delivery and misses out completely on this slower one.
Full and on the pads, Haris Rauf swings and misses. The ball rolls back to the keeper.
Back of a length, into the body. Haris Rauf slogs this behind mid-wicket for a couple of runs.

OUT! A FIFER FOR James Neesham! Good length on leg, Sufiyan Muqeem looks to clear the fence down the ground but the ball gets more elevation than distance and Michael Bracewell running in from long on takes it easily.
Sufiyan Muqeem c M Bracewell b J Neesham 0 (2b 0x4 0x6)
Good length around off, Haris Rauf punches this towards off for one.
BYE! Good length, around leg, Sufiyan Muqeem looks to slog this to leg but misses and the run as the keeper collects it.

OUT! A massive scalp for New Zealand as they remove Salman Agha who could have added a lot more at the end. Short-pitched, around off, Salman Agha moves to his leg and cuts this aiming for the stands. The ball goes straight into the hands of Mark Chapman at deep point and he has to walk back now.
Salman Agha (c) c M Chapman b J Neesham 51 (39b 6x4 1x6)

A brilliant effort from Ben Sears diving to his left at cover, but he fails to pouch this one. On a length around off, Salman Agha smashes this aerially but wide to the left of cover and Ben gets a hand behind it but the ball pops out. No run taken.
FOUR! On a length around off, Salman Agha setlles well behind this and lofts this over over for a boundary to begin the 19th.
Back of a length around middle and off, Haris Rauf gives it a proper whack but fails to connect.
Short-pitched, around off, Salman Agha fends this through mid-wicket for one. Agha was keen on the second but Haris Rauf had slipped as he was turning for the second and they settle for a single.
Good length on off, Salman Agha dabs this to short third for no run.
Yorker on leg, following the batter to his leg. Salman Agha blocks this out on off.
FOUR! That's some stroke from the Pakistan skipper. Pitched-up around off, Salman Agha moves away from the line of it this time around and gently chips this over cover for a boundary.

FOUR! Salman Agha takes the attack to Ben Sears straightaway. Good length on the pads, Salman Agha moves inside the line of it and flicks this over backward square leg for four runs. Salman Agha will be looking to make this positive start count for his side.

What a tremendous over from James Neesham. A double wicket over and things are looking gloomy for Pakistan once again in this contest. Good length around off, Haris Rauf looks to poke at it but misses out.
Short and wide outside off, Haris Rauf looks to cut this but misses out.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Another one for Neesham and he continues his good work with the ball. Good length around off, Jahandad Khan looks to slog this over mid-wicket but he balloons this off the outside off his bat over mid off for a simple catch to Will O'Rourke.
Jahandad Khan c W O'Rourke b J Neesham 1 (2b 0x4 0x6)
Good length around off, Salman Agha guides this to deep third for one.

Almost a disaster for Pakistan. Good length on off, Jahandad Khan dabs this to silly point and runs. James Neesham gives it a go and tries to run Agha out at the striker's end with a casual flick but misses barely.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Neesham strikes and breaks a potentially threatening partnership. Good length on off, Shadab Khan looks to slog this across the line and gets a faint edge which is taken cleanly by Mitchell Hay behind the stumps.
Shadab Khan c M Hay b J Neesham 28 (20b 5x4 0x6)

5 WIDES! Pressure on James Neesham straightaway. Way too wide outside off, Shadab Khan moves to his off and leaves it. The ball lands just on the pitch and it keeps going away from he keeper's reach for a boundary behind the stumps towards third man region.
FOUR! Tossed up around off, Salman Agha jumps to the pitch of it and lofts this over cover for a boundary more. 14 comes off this Ish Sodhi over.
Floated on the pads, Shadab Khan tucks this through square leg for one.
FOUR! Another one races away to the fence for four. Short of a length around off, Shadab Khan moves to his leg and cuts this through point for a boundary.
FOUR! Shadab finds the fence again. Tossed up around off, Shadab Khan moves to his leg, clears his front foot and slogs this down the ground for a boundary to long on.
Tossed up around off, Salman Agha shimmies down the ground and drills this off the inside to long off for one. It gave an impression of a wrong'un.
Pushed through on middle and leg, Salman Agha thumps this to cover-point for no run.

FOUR! Boundaries are coming in a hurry now. Good length around middle and leg, Shadab Khan slogs this one. Gets it barely over mid-wicket and the ball races after bouncing behind mid-wicket to the fence for four runs.
WIDE! Short-pitched, down the leg. Shadab Khan looks to hit this but misses out. Wided.
Short-pitched, around leg, Salman Agha gets it away to fine leg for one.

SIX! Finally, Salman Agha gets one away for a biggie. Short-pitched, wide of off, Salman Agha moves to his leg, opens up the off side and cuts this well. The ball sails over the fence and into the stand for six over deep point.
Good length around off, Shadab Khan punches this to sweeper cover for a single.
Good length on off, Salman Agha guides this through backward point for a single.
Short-pitched, around middle and leg, Salman Agha goes for the pull but gets a top edge behind the keeper for a couple.
Another one, pitched short and around off this time. Shadab Khan slashes hard but gets beaten.
Too full on the pads, Salman Agha flicks this through mid-wicket for one.
Short-pitched, around middle and leg, Salman Agha moves to his leg and looks to cut this over point but gets beaten.
Good length around off, Salman Agha defends this out on off.
Good length, around middle and leg, Shadab Khan moves to his leg and tucks this through mid on for one.
On a length around off, Salman Agha drives this to sweeper cover for one.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Shadab Khan shuffles across and cuts this past backward point for a boundary. Shadab isn't comfortable at all, but he still manages to score somehow.
Good length around leg, Shadab Khan goes for the pull but gets a top edge that lands just away from the reach of Mitchell Hay, who gave it a good chase towards square leg.
Short-pitched, around off, Shadab Khan runs down the track and looks to smash this down the ground but misses out.
On a length around off, Salman Agha smashes this to deep point for one.

Good length on the pads, Shadab Khan looks to flick this towards fine leg but gets it away off the gloves and Mitchell Hay behind the stumps dive to his left and fields this, keeping it down to a single.
Good length around off, Shadab Khan looks to slog this out of the park but gets an inside edge onto his pads for no run.
Wrong'un wide outside off, Shadab Khan drags this with a slog towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! A brilliantly struck boundary by Shadab Khan. Tossed up around off, Shadab Khan shuffles to his leg and drives this all along the carpet through cover for four.
Too full around off, Shadab Khan defends this out well.
OUTFOXED! A googly right on off, gets a bit of extra bounce. Shadab Khan looks to jam this down but gets beaten on the inside and the ball has barely missed the top of off.
Too full on the pads, Salman Agha goes for the sweep, loses his balance and falls over but manages to sneak a single to square leg.
Floated around middle and leg, Salman Agha punches this to off for no run.
Back of a length on off, Shadab blocks it out on off.
Good length arond off, Shadab Khan guides this off his back foot towards backward point for no run.
Back of a length arond off, Salman Agha guides this towards point and takes one.
Good length on off, Shadab Khan dabs this to third man region for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Good length wide outside off, Abdul Samad slashes and slashes hard at it but manages to slash underneath the ball and gets it off the top edge into the gloves of Mitchell Hay behind the stumps. Abdul did try to give a poker face to the umpire but he raises his finger and Samad walks back.
Abdul Samad c M Hay b J Neesham 4 (9b 0x4 0x6)
Back of a length around off, Abdul Samad dabs this to backward point.
Floated too full, at the stumps. Abdul Samad looks to heave it across the line but gets the inside edge that rolls to short fine leg for one.
Tossed up wrong'un, on the middle and leg. Salman Agha gets across and nudges into the leg side for a quick single.
Flatter and quicker at the stumps. Abdul Samad hacks it through mid-wicket for a single. Brings up the fifty for Pakistan.
Drops it short, on the leg stump line. Salman Agha goes back and pulls this to deep square leg for one.
Floated on off. Eased to long-off for one.
Flatter on off. Salman Agha knocks this to deep mid-on for one.
Short of a length, on the middle and leg stump line. Abdul Samad sways out of the line and lets it go. A dot to end the over.
Back of a length angled into the leg pole. Salman Agha tucks it round the corner for a single.
Short of a length delivery, angled into the body. Abdul Samad stays back and guides it past the first slip toward deep third for a single.
Back of a length again, on off. Abdul Samad defends into the off-side.
Back of a length, around off. Salman Agha runs it down to deep third for a single.
Short of a length, rising delivery, just outside off. Salman Agha has a poke at it and gets beaten.
Tossed up full, outside off. Abdul Samad comes forward and bunts into covers.

HOLES OUT! Usman Khan stands in disbelief. Ish Sodhi bowls a half-tracker, around the off-stump line. Usman Khan goes back and looks to power it over the ropes. Fails to get the desired connection and is caught near the wide long-on boundary by Daryl Mitchell.  Ish Sodhi gets among the wickets. Pakistan slide further.
Usman Khan c D Mitchell b I Sodhi 7 (7b 1x4 0x6)
Shortish leg break, outside off. Salman Agha cuts it off the outside edge to short third for a quick single.
Flatter on the middle stump line. Salman Agha brings out the reverse hit but mistimes it to short third.
Googly, on the middle and leg. Usman Khan tucks it through square leg for one.
FOUR! Punished! Short and wide outside off. Usman Khan stays back and cuts it hard through covers for a cracking boundary.
Fuller than a length, around off. Usman Khan makes room and cuts this to deep third for a single. Lovely work from Jacob Duffy near the ropes to keep this to a single.
Back of a length delivery, outside off. Usman Khan looks to cut but misses.
Short of a length angled into the middle. Salman Agha pulls it off the cue end toward fine leg for a single.
FOUR MORE! Nicely Done! Back of a length delivery, around off. Salman Agha hangs back and deliberately guides it off the edge over the first slip fielder for back to back boundaries.
FOUR! Up and Over! Short of a length delivery, outside off. Salman Agha uses the pace, throws hands at it, and cuts it over backward point for a boundary.
Back of a length delivery outside off. Salman Agha looks to guide it down but does not connect.
Short of a length, just outside off. Salman Agha rides the bounce and guides it to deep third for a single.
In the air but safe! Back of a length, angled into the middle. Usman Khan goes for the pull but miscues it just over the mid-wicket fielder for a single.
Back of a length, angled into the middle. Usman Khan is hurried up and mistimes the shot to square leg.

OUT! CAUGHT DOWN THE LEG! Jacob Duffy strikes! A loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved! Short of a good length, angled into the middle and leg. Omair Yousuf gets across the line and looks to help it over the keeper but might have gotten a faint edge on the way to Mitchell Hay. New Zealand are confident and they go upstairs to have a look. The replays show a clear spike on the glove and Omair Yousuf is a goner. Pakistan are three down.
Omair Yousuf c M Hay b J Duffy 7 (11b 0x4 0x6)
Back of a length delivery angled into the middle and leg. Salman Agha advances and taps into the off-side for one.
Short of a length delivery, angled into the middle stump line. Omair Yousuf backs away and guides it toward deep third for a single.
Short of a good length, on off. Salman Agha comes forward and defends.

OUT! MOHAMMAD HARIS DEPARTS! Short and quick outside off. Haris pulls and it flies straight up in the air off the top edge. The keeper, Mitchell Hay races to his left, settles under it, and takes a good catch with the gloves. Both the openers are back in the hut.
Mohammad Haris (wk) c M Hay b B Sears 11 (17b 2x4 0x6)
Fuller than a length outside off. Mohammad Haris slashes at it but does not connect.
Back of a length delivery, around off. Omair Yousuf rides the bounce and runs it down to deep third for one.

Oops! That must have hurt! Back of a length just outside off. Mohammad Haris steps across and looks to whip it over the backward square leg. It rears sharply and strikes him on the chest and they take a single into the leg side.
Short of a good length, outside off. Mohammad Haris swings and misses.
WIDE! Full and angling down the leg. Mohammad Haris swings and misses. Wide to start the over.
LEG BYE! Goes full, just outside off. Mohammad Haris gets across for the flick but misses and wears on the pad. The ball rolls into the off-side for a leg bye.
Duffy goes full and goes past the leg stump. Mohammad Haris advances for the drive but fails to make the connection.
FOUR! Nicely Done! Hard-length delivery, angled into the middle and leg. Mohammad Haris gets inside the line and helps it toward fine leg for a clever boundary.
Short of a good length, around off. Mohammad Haris looks to cut but fails to make any contact.
What a Ripper! Back of a length delivery, just outside off. Mohammad Haris looks to play at it but drops his wrists at the last moment and the ball goes past the outside edge.
Fuller than a length, moving away, outside off. Omair Yousuf guides it to deep third for a single.
Short of a good length, outside off. Mohammad Haris advances to flay it through covers but fails to make any contact.
FOUR! Not convincing but gets the result! Back of a length delivery, just outside off. Mohammad Haris gets across and pulls it off the inner half through the backward square leg for a boundary.
Back of a length delivery around off. Omair Yousuf runs it down to deep third for a single.
Short of a good length, just outside off. Omair Yousuf mistimes the cut shot into covers.
WIDE! Bowls it full and sliding down the leg. Omair Yousuf flicks and misses. Nice take by Mitchell Hay behind the stumps.
Short of a length, around off. Omair Yousuf cuts and misses.
Good length delivery outside off. Omair Yousuf looks to drive on the up but makes no contact.
Back of a length delivery, on a hard-length, outside off. Omair Yousuf stays back and carves it aerially, goes on the bounce to deep third for one.
Back of a length delivery, outside off. Omair Yousuf runs it down to the left of the third man and sprints back for a second.
Back of a length angled into the leg. Omair Yousuf looks to pull but gets stuck around the stomach.

OUT! SHARP CATCH! Jacob Duffy draws first blood. Bowls it on a length, on the middle and leg stump line. Hasan Nawaz looks to play across the line and closes the bat's face early. The ball takes the outside edge and flies toward the first slip where James Neesham dives to his left and takes a brilliant grab. Hasan Nawaz departs for a duck, his third in five games. Pakistan are rocked early.
Hasan Nawaz c J Neesham b J Duffy 0 (3b 0x4 0x6)
Lands it short of a length and just outside the off-stump. Hasan Nawaz makes room and takes a wild mow down the ground but isn't close to making contact.
WIDE! Hard-length delivery angled down the leg. Hasan Nawaz plays and misses at it. Wide signaled.
Peach! Pitched up and swinging away sharply outside off. Hasan Nawaz follows it and is beaten past the outside edge.

Mohammad Haris steps a long way across the crease outside off and O'Rourke follows him with a back of the length delivery. Haris shapes to scoop but ends up getting in a tangle as it passes the outside edge.
Back of a length delivery, outside off. Mohammad Haris slashes at it but does not connect.
Fuller than a length, outside off. Mohammad Haris swings and misses.
Short of a length delivery, angling in and going past the left shoulder. Mohammad Haris was asking for a wide but the umpire decides against it.
Short of a length, around off. Mohammad Haris has a poke at it and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length delivery, outside the off-stump. Mohammad Haris plays away from the body and guides it over the backward point fielder for a couple to get off the mark.
WIDE! A similar delivery moving outside the tramline. Mohammad Haris sways out of the line and lets it go. Another wide signaled by the umpire.
WIDE! Back of a length delivery, shaping away outside the tramline. Mohammad Haris flays and misses. Wide to start the innings.
